  "prompt": "What is macro in MS Excel?",
  "response": "In Microsoft Excel, a macro is a series of instructions that automate repetitive tasks or perform complex operations within a spreadsheet. Here are key points about macros:\n\n1. Definition\n- A set of programmed instructions that can perform multiple tasks automatically\n- Written in Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) programming language\n\n2. Purpose\n- Simplify repetitive tasks\n- Reduce manual data entry\n- Perform complex calculations\n- Automate spreadsheet operations\n- Save time and increase productivity\n\n3. Creating Macros\n- Can be recorded using Excel's macro recorder\n- Can be written manually using VBA code\n- Accessible through Developer tab in Excel\n\n4. Common Uses\n- Formatting data\n- Data validation\n- Generating reports\n- Performing complex calculations\n- Manipulating worksheets\n- Transferring data between sheets\n\n5. Benefits\n- Increases efficiency\n- Reduces human error\n- Allows complex operations\n- Consistent task execution\n- Customizable to specific needs\n\n6. Limitations\n- Requires basic programming knowledge\n- Potential security risks\n- Can be complex for advanced operations\n\n7. Activation\n- Can be run through keyboard shortcuts\n- Can be attached to buttons or form controls\n\nMacros are powerful tools for Excel users to streamline their spreadsheet work.",
